---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Affiliate Disclosure — Online Marketing Directory"
  description="Our affiliate disclosure policy. Learn how we earn commissions and how that affects our recommendations."
>
  <h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
  <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: January 1, 2024</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    Online Marketing Directory ("we," "our," or "this site") participates in various affiliate
    marketing programs. This means we may earn a commission when you click on certain links on
    this website and subsequently make a purchase or sign up for a service.
  </p>
  <p>
    This disclosure is provided in accordance with the Federal Trade Commission's 16 CFR, Part 255:
    "Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in Advertising."
  </p>

  <h2>What This Means for You</h2>
  <p>
    When you click on an affiliate link and make a purchase or sign up for a service, we may
    receive a commission. <strong>This comes at no additional cost to you.</strong> In many cases,
    affiliate partners offer exclusive discounts or extended trial periods through our links.
  </p>
  <p>
    The commission we earn helps support the ongoing operation of this site, including the time
    spent researching, testing, and writing reviews.
  </p>

  <h2>Our Review Standards</h2>
  <p>
    We are committed to honest, unbiased reviews regardless of whether an affiliate relationship
    exists. Specifically:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>We only recommend tools and programs we believe provide genuine value.</li>
    <li>Affiliate relationships do not influence our editorial opinions or ratings.</li>
    <li>We will note on each tool or training page whether an affiliate relationship exists.</li>
    <li>We decline affiliate partnerships for tools we would not personally recommend.</li>
    <li>Our "Not Ideal For" sections exist to give you an honest picture of each product's limitations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Which Links Are Affiliate Links?</h2>
  <p>
    Tool and training pages that include affiliate links are marked with a disclosure note on the
    individual page. "View Tool," "Learn More," and "Get Started" buttons typically contain affiliate
    links. Links within blog posts may also be affiliate links when they direct you to a product
    or service we recommend.
  </p>
  <p>
    We use <code>rel="sponsored"</code> attributes on affiliate links as required by search engine
    guidelines.
  </p>

  <h2>Affiliate Programs We Participate In</h2>
  <p>
    We may participate in affiliate programs for many of the tools listed in our directory,
    including but not limited to course platforms, email marketing services, design tools,
    and online business training programs. The specific programs change over time as we add
    new tools to the directory.
  </p>

  <h2>Your Trust Matters</h2>
  <p>
    We take our responsibility to provide honest, accurate information seriously. If you ever
    feel a review is inaccurate or that we've missed something important, please
    <a href="/contact">contact us</a>. We welcome feedback and correction.
  </p>

  <h2>Questions?</h2>
  <p>
    If you have any questions about our affiliate relationships or how they affect our content,
    please <a href="/contact">get in touch</a>. We're happy to provide additional information.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
